>After some attempts by browser vendors to create a standardand subsequent slow progressfront-end developers realized it was up to them to create a browser-agnostic library delivering on the promise of the web components vision. When React was released, it completely changed the paradigm of web development in two key ways. First, with a bit of JavaScript and some XML-like syntax, React allowed you to compose custom HTML tags it called components:

